thread.title: How big of an underdog is against Michigan State?
thread.title_full: How big of an underdog is Rutgers against Michigan State? | NJ.com

author: Dan Duggan | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: How big of an underdog is against Michigan State?
text:
PISCATAWAY â€” Rutgers hasn't yet demonstrated the ability to compete with the top teams in the Big Ten, so it's no surprise that No. 4 Michigan State opened as a heavy favorite for Saturday's matchup at High Point Solutions Stadium (8 p.m., BTN).
But the Spartans' inability to blowout inferior opponents has kept the line respectable, as Michigan State is favored by 17 points, according to vegasinsider.com
The Spartans are 5-0 (1-0 Big Ten) this season, but remarkably they are 0-5 against the spread. The oddsmakers finally reigned things in this week after Michigan State failed to cover spreads of at least 23 points in the past three games.
Listed as 23-point favorites, the Spartans squeaked out a 24-21 win over Purdue on Saturday. Michigan State's biggest win was a 20-point triumph over Central Michigan on Sept. 26.
The Spartans were 22-point favorites over Rutgers in their matchup last November. Michigan State easily covered in a 45-3 win .
